        <num title="1514">RESOLUTION NO. 1514</num>
        <speech by="#4c929028-e1d5-46a9-9075-8620e1ec2e77">
          <from>HON. FRANK CORBETT</from>
          <p>HON. FRANK CORBETT : Mr. Speaker, on behalf of the Premier, I hereby give notice that on a future day I shall move the adoption of the following resolution:</p>
        </speech>
        <speech by="#75109949-5b99-4b9c-b9fd-d85a8ce227ab">
          <from>MR. SPEAKER</from>
          <p>MR. SPEAKER : There has been a request for waiver.</p>
        </speech>
        <speech by="#4c929028-e1d5-46a9-9075-8620e1ec2e77">
          <from>HON. FRANK CORBETT</from>
          <p>HON. FRANK CORBETT : Mr. Speaker, with the concurrence of the House, would you please revert to the order of business, Tabling Reports, Regulations and Other Papers.</p>
        </speech>
        <speech by="#75109949-5b99-4b9c-b9fd-d85a8ce227ab">
          <from>MR. SPEAKER</from>
          <p>MR. SPEAKER : Would all those in favour of the motion please say Aye. Contrary minded, Nay.</p>
        </speech>
      </debateSection>
      <debateSection>
        <heading>TABLING REPORTS, REGULATIONS AND OTHER PAPERS</heading>
        <speech by="#75109949-5b99-4b9c-b9fd-d85a8ce227ab">
          <from>MR. SPEAKER</from>
          <p>MR. SPEAKER : The honourable Minister of Labour and Advanced Education.</p>
        </speech>
        <speech by="#dec41d7a-1f3f-40db-bdc4-d55134cb9a68">
          <from>HON. MARILYN MORE</from>
          <p>HON. MARILYN MORE : Mr. Speaker, I wonder if I might be permitted to make an introduction before tabling the report.</p>
        </speech>
        <speech by="#75109949-5b99-4b9c-b9fd-d85a8ce227ab">
          <from>MR. SPEAKER</from>
          <p>MR. SPEAKER : Most certainly.</p>
        </speech>
        <speech by="#dec41d7a-1f3f-40db-bdc4-d55134cb9a68">
          <from>MS. MORE</from>
          <p>MS. MORE : Thank you. Mr. Speaker, in your gallery this afternoon we are honoured to have with us the president of the Nova Scotia Community College, Don Bureaux. He was appointed president of the college last year, a very well-deserved appointment following a long career with the Nova Scotia Community College that goes back to 2004. He has been working with learners for many years.</p>
        </speech>
        <speech by="#75109949-5b99-4b9c-b9fd-d85a8ce227ab">
          <from>MR. SPEAKER</from>
          <p>MR. SPEAKER : We welcome all our guests to the gallery and hope they enjoy this afternoon's proceedings.</p>
        </speech>
        <speech by="#dec41d7a-1f3f-40db-bdc4-d55134cb9a68">
          <from>HON. MARILYN MORE</from>
          <p>HON. MARILYN MORE : Mr. Speaker, I wish to table the 2012 Annual Report for the Nova Scotia Community College.</p>
        </speech>
        <speech by="#75109949-5b99-4b9c-b9fd-d85a8ce227ab">
          <from>MR. SPEAKER</from>
          <p>MR. SPEAKER : The report is tabled.</p>
        </speech>
      </debateSection>
