        <speech by="#8a8470fb-0e2f-4e9e-8810-4f20c748d898">
          <from>HON. KAREN CASEY</from>
          <p>HON. KAREN CASEY : Mr. Speaker, with your permission I would like to make an introduction.</p>
        </speech>
        <speech by="#75109949-5b99-4b9c-b9fd-d85a8ce227ab">
          <from>MR. SPEAKER</from>
          <p>MR. SPEAKER : Most certainly.</p>
        </speech>
        <speech by="#8a8470fb-0e2f-4e9e-8810-4f20c748d898">
          <from>MS. CASEY</from>
          <p>MS. CASEY : I would like to draw the attention of the members to the gallery opposite where we have a special guest here - no stranger to the members of this House, Pam Murchison is here. Pam, as you will recall, is the mother of Jenna, who took her life as a result of cyberbullying. Pam has been an advocate for youth and she presents herself in many schools from Yarmouth to Sydney where she speaks to students to try to help them understand and to let them know there is someone who cares.</p>
        </speech>
        <speech by="#75109949-5b99-4b9c-b9fd-d85a8ce227ab">
          <from>MR. SPEAKER</from>
          <p>MR. SPEAKER : We welcome all our guests to the gallery and hope they enjoy this afternoon's proceedings.</p>
        </speech>
